FBIS3-4285 "drchi060_d_94004" FBIS-CHI-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Mar 1994 Northeast Asia Beijing TV Reports Ceremony OW2803165194 Beijing Central Television Program One Network in Mandarin 1100 GMT 28 Mar 94 OW2803165194 Beijing Central Television Program One Network in Mandarin 1100 GMT 28 Mar 94 Language: Mandarin Article Type:BFN [From the "National News Hookup" program] [Text] At the invitation of State President Jiang Zemin, ROK President Kim Yong-sam began an official visit to China on 26 March. This afternoon, President Jiang Zemin presided over a ceremony at the Great Hall of the People to warmly welcome President Kim Yong-sam and his wife. Present at the welcoming ceremony were Tian Jiyun, vice chairman of the National People's Congress Standing Committee; Qian Qichen, vice premier of the State Council and minister of foreign affairs; Wu Jichuan, chairman of the Chinese Government Reception Committee and minister of posts and communications; Li Ganliu, vice chairman of the Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang; Li Zhongli, minister of finance; Wang Zhongyu, minister in charge of the State Economic and Trade Commission; Liu Zhongde, minister of culture; and other officials. Principal members of President Kim Yong-sam's entourage included Minister of Foreign Affairs Han Sung-chu. Born in 1927 on Geoje Island in the ROK's South Kyongsang Province, Kim Yong-sam was elected a member of the 14th parliament, president of the Democratic Liberal Party [DLP], and DLP presidential candidate in 1992. He later became the 14th president of the ROK in December 1992.
